<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-49-0141 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper presents the first version of an econometric model of the FRGenergy-sector, which was built on behalf of the Federal Ministry of Economics.The model is characteristic in that its demand side connects input-outputtables and energy balances which provides the analysis of the links betweenthe energy sector and the rest of the economy. The supply side of themodel provides the analysis of technological or political restrictions.It models demand for 14 supplies of energy in 13 sectors and calculatedin a conversion-model the energy supply necessary to meet demand. Thisis illustrated by analysing the demand for space-heating and petrol inprivate households and industry. Estimation period of the model presentedis 1962 to 1981. Ex-post-simulations indicate a satisfying explanatorypower.</TEXT></DOC>